data.description: With this setting the extrusion on printed parts is reduced where the print head has to go over a thin area twice. This way all walls are printed without the part being over extruded. The setting can be enabled for the outer or the inner walls separately.
data.img_description: This image illustrates a thin wall being printed with overlapping wall compensation enabled.
data.hints: - With this option enabled, print paths stay unaffected. Only the extrusion rate over the printed path is affected.
